Here's a link to the stackoverflow question about this: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/17333531/how-can-i-display-the-current-branch-and-folder-path-in-terminal


If you're using a bash shell you can just add the whole block of gibberish below to your ~/.bash_profile

parse_git_branch() {
    git branch 2> /dev/null | sed -e '/^[^*]/d' -e 's/* \(.*\)/ (\1)/'
}

export PS1="\u@\h \[\033[32m\]\w - \$(parse_git_branch)\[\033[00m\] $ "

save it, and source it (via "source ~/.bash_profile")
